ary":"Théobald DE CREPY II是Adam DE CRÉPY的儿子，于1075年出生在法国皮卡迪奧易可雷--瓦洛易斯。他于1095年与Elisabeth Gauthier DE CHÂTILLON在法国皮卡迪奧易南托易爾勒-豪度易结婚。他们至少是2个女儿的父母。他去世于1141年在法国皮卡迪奧易南托易爾勒-豪度易享年66岁。"},"hr":{"1075–1141":"1075.–1141.","1075–Female":"1075.–preminula","1095–Female":"1095.–preminula","1105–1180":"1105.–1180","1045–1120":"1045–1120","1105":"1105.","about 1095":"oko 1095.","circa 1120":"oko 1120.","1045":"1045","1120":"1120","1075":"1075.","1141":"1141.","1095":"1095.","1180":"1180","Nanteuil-Le-Haudouin, Oise, Picardie, France":"Nanteuil-le-Haudouin, Oise, Picardie, Francuska","Frankrijk":"Francuska","Crépy-en-Valois, Oise, Picardie, France":"Crépy-en-Valois, Oise, Picardie, Francuska"},"cs":{"1075–1141":"1075–1141","1075–Female":"1075–Zesnulá","1095–Female":"1095–Zesnulá","1105–1180":"1105–1180","1045–1120":"1045–1120","1105":"1105","about 1095":"okolo 1095","circa 1120":"okolo 1120","1045":"1045","1120":"1120","1075":"1075","1141":"1141","1095":"1095","1180":"1180","Nanteuil-Le-Haudouin, Oise, Picardie, France":"Nanteuil-le-Haudouin, Oise, Picardie, Francie","Frankrijk":"Francie","Crépy-en-Valois, Oise, Picardie, France":"Crépy-en-Valois, Oise, Picardie, Francie"},"da":{"1075–1141":"1075–1141","1075–Female":"1075–Afdød","1095–Female":"1095–Afdød","1105–1180":"1105–1180","1045–1120":"1045–1120","1105":"1105","about 1095":"omkring 1095","circa 1120":"omkring 1120","1045":"1045","1120":"1120","1075":"1075","1141":"1141","1095":"1095","1180":"1180","Nanteuil-Le-Haudouin, Oise, Picardie, France":"Nanteuil-le-Haudouin, Oise, Picardie, Frankrig","Frankrijk":"Frankrig","Crépy-en-Valois, Oise, Picardie, France":"Crépy-en-Valois, Oise, Picardie, Frankrig"},"nl":{"1075–1141":"1075–1141","1075–Female":"1075–Overleden","1095–Female":"1095–Overleden","1105–1180":"1105–1180","1045–1120":"1045–1120","1105":"1105","about 1095":"circa 1095","circa 1120":"circa 1120","1045":"1045","1120":"1120","1075":"1075","1141":"1141","1095":"1095","1180":"1180","Nanteuil-Le-Haudouin, Oise, Picardie, France":"Nanteuil-le-Haudouin, Oise, Picardie, Frankrijk","Frankrijk":"Frankrijk","Crépy-en-Valois, Oise, Picardie, France":"Crépy-en-Valois, Oise, Picardie, Frankrijk"},"en":{"1075–1141":"1075–1141","1075–Female":"1075–Deceased","1095–Female":"1095–Deceased","1105–1180":"1105–1180","1045–1120":"1045–1120","1105":"1105","about 1095":"about 1095","circa 1120":"about 1120","1045":"1045","1120":"1120","1075":"1075","1141":"1141","1095":"1095","1180":"1180","Nanteuil-Le-Haudouin, Oise, Picardie, France":"Nanteuil-le-Haudouin, Oise, Picardie, France","Frankrijk":"France","Crépy-en-Valois, Oise, Picardie, France":"Crépy-en-Valois, Oise, Picardie, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"DE","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"CREPY","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Americanized form of German   Krebs   or of its variant   Kreps  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Krebs","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Hans, Gerhard, Arno, Bernd, Dieter, Erwin, Franz, Fritz, Heinz, Helmut, Irmgard.","German and Swiss German: metonymic occupational name for a catcher or seller of crabs or crayfish or a nickname for someone thought to resemble a crab, perhaps because they had a peculiar gait. The name was certainly standardized from older variants like <i>Krevetes</i> or <i>Krebiss</i> which reflect Middle Low German <i>crevet</i> ‘crab, shrimp’, as well as Middle High German <i>krebez</i>. This surname is also found in e.g. Slovenia, Czechia, and Poland, often as a translation into German of the Slavic surname   Rak   ‘crayfish’, and in France (mainly Alsace and Lorraine). Compare   Crabbs  ,   Crapps  ,   Crepps  ,   Creps  , and   Krebbs  .","Jewish (Ashkenazic): artificial name from German <i>Krebs</i> ‘crab’ (see 1 above)."]}]},{"name":"Théobald","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>þeud</i> ‘people, race’ + <i>bald</i> ‘bold, brave’. The first element was altered under the influence of Greek <i>theos</i> ‘god’. This name was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Théobald DE CREPY II was born in 1075, in Crépy-en-Valois, Oise, Picardie, France as the son of Adam DE CRÉPY. He married Elisabeth Gauthier DE CHÂTILLON in 1095, in Nanteuil-le-Haudouin, Oise, Picardie, France. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. He died in 1141, in Nanteuil-le-Haudouin, Oise, Picardie, France, at the age of 66."},"et":{"1075–1141":"1075–1141","1075–Female":"1075–Surnud","1095–Female":"1095–Surnud","1105–1180":"1105–1180","1045–1120":"1045–1120","1105":"1105","about 1095":"umbes 1095","circa 1120":"umbes 1120","1045":"1045","1120":"1120","1075":"1075","1141":"1141","1095":"1095","1180":"1180","Nanteuil-Le-Haudouin, Oise, Picardie, France":"Nanteuil-le-Haudouin, Oise, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Frankrijk":"Prantsusmaa","Crépy-en-Valois, Oise, Picardie, France":"Crépy-en-Valois, Oise, Picardie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1075–1141":"1075–1141","1075–Female":"1075–Kuollut","1095–Female":"1095–Kuollut","1105–1180":"1105–1180","1045–1120":"1045–1120","1105":"1105","about 1095":"noin 1095","circa 1120":"noin 1120","1045":"1045","1120":"1120","1075":"1075","